IRS990.MissionDesc: WE HELP COMMUNITY FOUNDATIONS BUILD STRONG COMMUNITIES BY ADVANCING EFFECTIVE PRACTICES, SHARING KNOWLEDGE AND GALVANIZING ACTION ON CRITICAL ISSUES OF OUR TIME.
IRS990.Desc: POSITION COMMUNITY FOUNDATIONS ON ISSUES: PRIMARY FOCUS: FAMILY ECONOMIC SECURITY PROJECT, A RESEARCH PROJECT TO UNCOVER AND DOCUMENT COMMUNITY FOUNDATION ACTIVITIES TO INCREASE ECONOMIC SUCCESS OF LOW-INCOME FAMILIES. ANALYZED AND SUMMARIZED DATA FROM FIELD-WIDE SURVEY OF COMMUNITY FOUNDATIONS; CONDUCTED INTERVIEWS WITH COMMUNITY FOUNDATIONS ABOUT THEIR WORK IN THIS AREA; AND HELD REGIONAL MEETINGS IN MINNEAPOLIS, OAKLAND, WASHINGTON D.C., ATLANTA, AND DETROIT TO SHARE SURVEY FINDINGS AND DISCUSS CURRENT APPROACHES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: BUILDING ORGANIZATIONAL CAPACITY: PRIMARY FOCUS: MICHIGAN COMMUNITY LEADERSHIP NETWORK (cln), A LEARNING NETWORK TO HELP COMMUNITY FOUNDATIONS TO BUILD PEER CONNECTIONS AND ADVANCE THEIR COMMUNITY LEADERSHIP PRACTICE. PLANNED AND CONVENED TWO MEETINGS OF THE MICHIGAN CLN. OTHER CAPACITY-BUILDING INCLUDED CONSULTING SERVICES, A WEBINAR AND FACILITATED CEO VISITS. EXECUTIVE LEADERSHIP INSTITUTE FOR VICE PRESIDENTS, AN INTENSIVE LEARNING OPPORTUNITY TAILORED SPECIFICALLY FOR COMMUNITY FOUNDATION CEOS OR VPS WHO ARE EAGER TO MORE EFFECTIVELY ADDRESS DIFFICULT COMMUNITY LEADERSHIP CHALLENGES IN THEIR COMMUNITIES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: Promoting Community Leadership: KEY AREA OF FOCUS : FALL FORUM FOR COMMUNITY FOUNDATION CEO'S AND BOARD MEMBERS TO BUILD KNOWLEDGE OF COMMUNITY LEADERSHIP AND DISCUSS EMERGING ISSUES FACING COMMUNITIES. ALSO WORKED WITH THE INTER-AMERICAN FOUNDATION TO MANAGE AND FACILITATE A TRANSNATIONAL LEARNING YEAR WITH THE U.S. AND LATIN AMERICAN COMMUNITY FOUNDATIONS.

Annually, the committee shall review and approve CFLeads' IRS Form 990 and Circulate it to all members of the board before it is filed. The Committee shall report matters requiring the attention of the full board, at its discretion, at the first practical opportunity.
